## Step 3: Feature Reverse-Engineering

| Feature | Problem it Solves | How it works | Why it works (Behavior -> Result) |
|---------|-------------------|--------------|-----------------------------------|
| **Timeline Playback** | "I want to see *how* the fight unfolded, not just where it ended." | - Synchronizes all players by `ts`.<br>- Adjustable speed (1x-5x).<br>- Progress slider. | **User**: Understands player intent/pacing.<br>**Business**: Identifies churn-inducing map frustration. |
| **Heatmap Overlay** | "I can't tell which areas are busy across hundreds of matches." | - Aggregates densities into a grid.<br>- Color-coded intensity.<br>- Toggleable layer. | **User**: Pinpoints macro-level map issues.<br>**Business**: Faster balancing = more stable meta. |
| **Bot vs Human Toggle** | "I don't know if this path is weird because of a human or a bot bug." | - Color-coded paths.<br>- Filtering by `user_id` format. | **User**: Debugs AI navigation or human flow.<br>**Business**: Improves "believability" of Entity AI. |

