## Step 5: Top Problem Hypotheses

| Priority | Problem Hypothesis | Why I Picked It | Confidence |
|----------|--------------------|-----------------|------------|
| **P1** | Level Designers struggle to identify **"Dead Zones"** (ignored areas) because movement paths overlap heavily, making low-traffic areas indistinguishable from high-traffic ones. | Observed "spaghetti" effect in raw coordinate plots. | High |
| **P2** | Designers struggle to correlate **"Storm Pressure"** with player deaths because they can't easily see the storm's temporal movement relative to player positions. | Event data is point-in-time; needs temporal playback to understand "why". | High |
| **P3** | Stakeholders struggle to **"Share Insights"** because they have no way to link a specific match/event to a teammate. | Critical for collaborative map-making. | Medium |
